\n<Manu><WordWrap>It's been a while now already...
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>MANU!
\n<Manu><WordWrap>TOMAS?!
\n<Manu><WordWrap>What happened? You were out for so long, how are the other contestants, and the Capitol?
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Calm down Manu I'll explain everything I can.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>So after bringing the first contestant to the Capitol many were in shock and awe that the contestant was still alive.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>I was surrounded by many people. Before I got a chance to answer them I was able to escape and get to the cave as soon as possible.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>After that and delivering the other missing contestants, the people were swarming around us while questioning and thanking me that I was able to save them.

\n<Tomas><WordWrap>To cut the story short, I was able to discuss one of the heads of the Capitol and told them what you did and how you were able to save them. I mentioned that I only delivered them to the Capitol.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>They were grateful to you Manu. However they won't say anything about you for now at least.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Reason is that your still a contestant in this contest and people have a bad taste in their mouths on what had happened to the other contestants.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>So for now they're keeping the story under wraps for now. But the main headline of the story right now is the discovery of the lost contestants.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Manu I don't know how but I am...No, the whole island is grateful for your action.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>So what do you plan on doing now?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Since the contest is still going on. You already know what I'm going to do next.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>If your planning to find Esbeche, you better head to the caves of this island. There's a chance he might be trapped .
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>You better be careful out there Manu. You might get yourself hurt or trapped in the caves.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Thanks for the caution Tomas. But I'm here to finish what I started.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Time to find Esbeche.
Search for Esbeche inside of the caves

\n<Manu><WordWrap>Tomas, I got some news!
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>What is it Manu?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I found Esbeche!
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>WHAT? YOU DID?!
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I did but there's a catch...
\n<Manu><WordWrap>He'll only comeback if I made him Kinilaw and Grilled Bangus. He said that you know how to help me?
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>I think I understand what he meant by that.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Knowing Esbeche for years, he is the type of person who demands something for his dishes.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I can tell by the distraught in his voice.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Since Esbeche wants you to make his favorite dish Kinilaw and Grilled Bangus. He expects you the dishes are fresh.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Fresh?
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Fresh. He wants fresh fish caught. Reason is that the fresher the fish the more flavor it has in stored in its body. And that's why Esbeche is a troublesome person.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>He is obsessed with food being freshly caught from the ocean, and I cannot blame him. The fresher the fish the tastier it is.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Your best bet, is to catch the fish itself.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Here's a fishing rod and some bait for you to get some fish.
You Obtained 1x Fishing Rod and 30 Bait!!!
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>There are lakes scattered around the island that has different types of fishes in them.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Based on the dishes alone, I know where he is and the best way to catch the fish you need.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Head to the back of the restaurant. There should be a small bridge that you could firsh for Tuna and Bangus.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Be careful those fish are fast swimmers and tough to reel in with your rod. So you better have the speed and grip to catch the fish.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>If you caught both Tuna and Bangus. Come back to me so I can give you the recipe you need.
A

\n<Tomas><WordWrap>What is it Manu? Did Esbeche liked the dishes?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>He did! And not only tthat but he allowed me to pass to the next area of the contest!
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>That's great! But how do you know that your "allowed" to continue to the next area of the contest?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>He just told me, he said so and people wouldn't second guess his words.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Classic Esbeche, he's alway's serious when talking and demanding things. He can't even take a joke sometimes.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>But it's true. People would believe him cause of his serious nature.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Either way, congratulations on your winning Esbeche's favor Manu.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Continue your journey on the contest and while your at it, show them what you're made of.
\n<Tomas><WordWrap>Come by and visit us sometimes. We would like to have some company.
